FBIS4-16005 "drsov071_g_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-071 Daily Report 12 Apr 1994 WESTERN REGION Belarus BNF Nominates Paznyak, Promises `Civilized' Campaign BNF Nominates Paznyak, Promises `Civilized' Campaign WS1204111794 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1000 GMT 12 Apr 94 WS1204111794 Minsk Radio Minsk Network Belarusian BFN [Text] A session of the Council of the Belarusian Popular Front [BNF] was held in the conference hall of the Minsk Palace of Arts. The BNF delegates officially nominated their leader Zyanon Paznyak as a candidate in the upcoming presidential elections. In addition to this, a BNF statement was adopted. It states that the BNF will conduct a civilized election campaign, without discrediting and humiliating political opponents. The delegates have proposed that other Belarusian political parties and movements adopt corresponding statements.
